VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT \btry\s*{[^}]*new\s+\w+
WHEN EXPR MISSING:unique_ptr|shared_ptr|RAII|catch\s*\(std::bad_alloc
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects dynamic memory allocations inside `try` blocks that may lead to memory leaks if an exception is thrown.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Resource Leak on Exception.
